    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i guess. but if it only works when the big powers happen to agree, isn't it basically just a tool for those powers to act whenever they want? it feels like the \"legitimacy\" you're talking about is just a way to make a system that favors the strongest countries look more official than it actually is. is there really a valid historian's view that says the current structure is actually worth saving?",
